10/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The education ministers of the Federation of BiH and Republika Srpska signed a common school curriculum agreement in Sarajevo on Friday (8 August). All schools in BiH agreed to follow the programme during the school year that starts in September. The Office of the High Representative considers the document a major step forward in implementing education reforms. (FENA, BBC - 08/08/03)
